I have a question about AA. 
The first contract function call , "setSecondOwner", always fails.
But the second time, it works fine.
I thought it's because of the gas related params, because there is a extra deployment process at the first call and '@account-abstraction/sdk' hardcoded some gas calculations.
But even if I set high "maxPriorityFeePerGas", "maxFeePerGas", "verificationGasLimit", "preVerificationGas", it still fails.

If I call simply transfer at the first time, it works fine.  

Are there any possible reasons for this problem?

this is the transaction log.
It says only "success :False".
https://mumbai.polygonscan.com/tx/0x7dbf54eecfaf4afe3813075c577c9bed6a337772c5b5aacda3dc76b6fa0a5768#eventlog
Hey <@173910568640446464> is this from two-owner-account branch?

I have no ideaüò¢
We use Stackup bundler and entrypoint.  it's implementation problem?ü§î 
Our temporary solution is very ugly; simply send transactions twice.
https://github.com/enu-kuro/bailout/blob/240fdad12d49143de4ed7bbdb0f92595a5d843f6/packages/site/src/snapMock/aaWallet.ts#L86

What do you mean?
We implemented 2FA(multisig) in AA and encountered a problem to set the socondOwner during the first contract call.

Why are you creating `accountAPI` from `SimpleAccountAPI` You should be using your own API specific to your wallet. This will deploy the simpleAccount which doesn't have `setSecondOwner` function inside it

> You should be using your own API specific to your wallet.

I know but we don't have enough time to fully implement our own API.
In most cases, "@account-abstraction/sdk" works fine without customization.
The only modification we made was to use "myWrapProvider".
https://github.com/enu-kuro/bailout/blob/main/packages/site/src/snapMock/myWrapProvider.ts
Unfortunately, you will have to implement custom API. But you can fast track it by extending SimpleAccountAPI and modifying the functions that need change,

Hi - got some issue with trying out Trampoline. With the given Goerli setting (https://github.com/eth-infinitism/trampoline/blob/2b09df1da7e749dda821908f16465f4149ae549b/src/exconfig.ts), after filling some test ETH with the newly created account, I tried to deploy the account via "DEPLOY ACCOUNT" button (or send some ETH out to other addresses), the `txHash` returned `null`. See attached console screen.

I did the same with the current Sepolia setup (https://github.com/eth-infinitism/trampoline/blob/master/src/exconfig.ts) - it gave error instead - `4001: Invalid UserOp signature or paymaster signature`. Wonder if there is any pointer around such observation.
Hey! Our booth is right beside the mentors booth
Thanks for your question! We're getting in touch with the folks who built Trampoline, and will get back to you ASAP
Hey <@701416168505737217> did you make any changes to `account-api`?
no - just cloned from repo
umm, then it shouldn't have happened. what is your operating system?
MacOS
with Chrome as browser

<@701416168505737217>  try changing the `stateVersion` in `exconfig.ts` and restarting `yarn start` after compilation is complete try reloading it. Somehow your local state might have been corrupted, this would reset the state. I will try and do an RCA in the meantime to see why this might have happened.
You can bump it to `0.2`
`stateVersion` is a random version we give to the state we store in `localstorage` to be able to re-load the previous extension state. Changing it would just reset the state.

<@784463459218751528> 
Hi, I'm also working on the AA wallet extending the Trampoline wallet and need help.

I got this error when I call the function sends 0x as data from Trampoline.

```
{"message":"preVerificationGas too low: expected at least 45748","code":-32602}
```

We are working on a chain that StackUp does not support, so we are running a local bundler with --an unsafe option.

Hey <@531244382905565195>  are you on the latest pull? we added support for `eth_estimateUserOperation`.
If you are on the latest pull then this might be returning some wrong estimations.

For this you can checkout the blog https://mirror.xyz/erc4337official.eth/r0Sxa_ncYJA8y7_YHeKz9cShDgfTNR1fVBolcBN7VZ4 and search for `preVerificationGas`. 

You will have to try overwriting `createUnsignedUserOp` in account-api like how we  did it in the blog.

Thanks! We clone the repo yesterday, so it should be almost the latest commit, and I checked it is getting estimation from "eth_estimateUserOperation".

It looks like my local bundler currently giving a lower estimation, so I try to override it, thanks!!
changing `stateVersion` makes Sepolia setup work, but Goerli one still doesn't work (returning null)
I would still suggest taking a pull once. I have pushed a change just sometime ago
are you using stackup's bundler or running locally?
I suspected the old default config (https://github.com/eth-infinitism/trampoline/blob/2b09df1da7e749dda821908f16465f4149ae549b/src/exconfig.ts) no longer worked?
stackup bundler
The old config was for v0.5, we need to change addresses to support v0.6

Thanks, I can now send the tx with manual modification of the gas estimation!

I saw the commit, but I already modified a lot of code in our own repo, and bit difficult to pull the latest one now.

<@784463459218751528> 
I'm working on verifying Paymaster and I need to set paymasterAndData.

Is there any guide for that? I found a link in your blog, but this issue has no content.
https://github.com/eth-infinitism/trampoline/issues/4
working now with the stackup bundler also on v0.6
thank you for the help

There is no standard rpc call for setting `paymasterAndData` by the dapp as of now. I think once we have adoption then Dapps can use `eth_sendUserOperation` and specify `paymasterAndData`. I don't have the support for `eth_sendUserOperation` as of now. 

But if you want to set `paymasterAndData` as part of your wallet, then you can set it and return it in `createUnsignedUserOp` only.
If you do need support for a dapp to send `eth_sendUserOperation` let me know. I think I can make some changes quickly
Thanks, currently we are implementing paymasterAndData as part of my wallet, so I think I can insert simple paymasterAndData in createUnsignedUserOp process.

However, I think the current paymaster requires:

1. user signs the userOp with a blank paymaster signature
2. paymaster signs the userOp with a user signature from step.1
3. user signs the useOp with the signature from step.2

https://github.com/eth-infinitism/account-abstraction/blob/develop/contracts/samples/VerifyingPaymaster.sol

So I need to do one extra user signing process in Trampoline wallet for step.1.
Do you have any suggestion to sign the userOp for step.1?
I think we can add PaymasterAPI in accountAPI or sign directly with keyring, but it is a bit complex for me to analyze where to modify in Trampoline wallet.
We discovered an issue when using `@account-abstraction/sdk` in the browser: https://github.com/eth-infinitism/bundler/issues/107 . Workaround is also there

I think you don't need step 1. Also if you need to add paymasterAndData later, you will have to:

1. return dummy `paymasterAndData` in `createUnsignedUserOp` - this is to make sure we have correct gas estimations
2. return the actual `paymasterAndData` in `signUserOpWithContext`

Actually, I'm not very sure how to use Verifying Paymaster, but it looks like we need step 1 in the test code. I think that's required for sig verification to make sure paymaster sign for a specific account tx.

https://github.com/eth-infinitism/account-abstraction/blob/develop/test/verifying_paymaster.test.ts#L93

line 94-> step1
line 99-> step2
line 100-> step3
I'm getting a bit confused, can you please check the above test code of Infinitism team?

In this case you can return `paymasterAndData: hexConcat([paymaster.address, defaultAbiCoder.encode(['uint48', 'uint48'], [MOCK_VALID_UNTIL, MOCK_VALID_AFTER]), '0x' + '00'.repeat(65)])` in `createUnsignedUserOp`

while in `signUserOpWithContext` since you will get the complete `userOp` with dummy `paymasterAndData` you can first sign it using the owner and then later append the actual `paymasterAndData` and return the userOp
I am unsure of this, I will have to re-check this. But last I checked and worked with an older entryPoint and older verifyingPaymaster. I did not sign before the `paymasterAndData`
But if the tests work, you can use the way I described above to create a similar flow.

Thanks! 

I check the old version of verifying paymaster, and it looks like not having step1, so it maybe because of the version difference.
https://github.com/eth-infinitism/account-abstraction/blob/9b64a3c5dc0e9e2c4b9aa5cc834394ac66ed4fc2/contracts/samples/VerifyingPaymaster.sol

I found actual code sign the userOp with keyring, I try to check and modify around signUserOpWithContext.

Hi <@784463459218751528> - see if you can help. I got a custom Account contract, but when it tried to deploy the contract via the UI (by clicking DEPLOY ACCOUNT button). It resulted in a `AA23` error at `eth_estimateUserOperationGas`.  Looking at past post (e.g. https://github.com/eth-infinitism/account-abstraction/issues/263), as there is no revert reason, it seems to be related to gas limit. Is there any way to adjust the call gas limit?
thanks in advance
